<div id="review_1235989730" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1235989730" />
    <a title="Jenny Baker" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16404316-jenny-baker"><img alt="Jenny Baker" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1563044810p2/16404316.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1235989730?book_show_action=true">Nov 17, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jenny Baker" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jenny Baker" href="/user/show/16404316-jenny-baker">Jenny Baker</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16404316-jenny-baker?shelf=mystery-thrillers">mystery-thrillers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16404316-jenny-baker?shelf=audiobooks">audiobooks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16404316-jenny-baker?shelf=2019">2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16404316-jenny-baker?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1235989730" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1143439459215259634">The show Bosch on Amazon Prime is one of my favorite shows. Titus Welliver is the perfect Bosch and I recently learned that he narrates the Bosch novels that published after the show started. That’s something to look forward to!<br/><br/>Detective Harry Bosch is a lone wolf who likes to bend the rules, but it’s always for the sake of catching the criminal. He has many enemies in the department, people who are always trying to ruin him and his career, because some think he’s a suspect in different crimes, </span>
  <span id="freeText1143439459215259634" style="display:none">The show Bosch on Amazon Prime is one of my favorite shows. Titus Welliver is the perfect Bosch and I recently learned that he narrates the Bosch novels that published after the show started. That’s something to look forward to!<br /><br />Detective Harry Bosch is a lone wolf who likes to bend the rules, but it’s always for the sake of catching the criminal. He has many enemies in the department, people who are always trying to ruin him and his career, because some think he’s a suspect in different crimes, but he’s not guilty of any of them. <br /><br />Connelly carefully lays out the plots and eliminates just enough information that you can’t easily solve them. He uses simple language to paint a vivid setting and he only describes the essentials, so you’re not bogged down with unnecessary detail. The characters are authentic, each unique with distinct voices, and you never have to guess who’s speaking. I love how he tells a story and makes me feel like I’m right there next to the characters. Great writing. <br /><br />Overall, I love the start of this series and I’m looking forward to continuing it. Highly recommended.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1143439459215259634" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


