<span id="freeTextContainer12984490964308230504">I somehow got this onto my reading list a couple of years ago, <b>thinking it was sci-fi</b>.... Hahahaaaaha!<br/><br/>I was 50 pages in before I realised, &quot;Hey. There&apos;s no sci-fi here...&quot;, but too late... I was hooked! <br/><br/>What a great accident. <b> I then inhaled 16 of the Bosch books within 3 months </b> , and now have to wait like the rest of you for a year for each new story.<br/><br/>This is the first-ever published book by Michael Connelly, and it&apos;s a cracker! The pace picks up, the murder becomes two, and more complex, more </span>
  <span id="freeText12984490964308230504" style="display:none">I somehow got this onto my reading list a couple of years ago, <b>thinking it was sci-fi</b>.... Hahahaaaaha!<br /><br />I was 50 pages in before I realised, "Hey. There's no sci-fi here...", but too late... I was hooked! <br /><br />What a great accident. <b> I then inhaled 16 of the Bosch books within 3 months </b> , and now have to wait like the rest of you for a year for each new story.<br /><br />This is the first-ever published book by Michael Connelly, and it's a cracker! The pace picks up, the murder becomes two, and more complex, more red herrings, an FBI love interest well-handled, a terrific climax at the end, and then a superb twist.<br /><br />Well-drawn characters, wonderful descriptions of (Los Angeles, which city I do not know), and historical references and backgrounds to "tunnel rats" during the Vietnam War - fascinating and horrific.<br /><br />Excellent stuff. I will be reading more of the Harry Bosch stories now.<br /><br />Notes:<br /> 8.6% "I don't usually read detective books. TV -- I like the complicated ones. I somehow thought this was sci-fi, who knows. Anyway, was going to abandon it, but read on the bus today for 90 mins and it's pretty good. Will probably stick with it until The Boss becomes cliché obnoxious :("<br /><br /> 30.4% "After about page 50-60 the pace picks up very nicely, the mystery deepens and the love interest enters the scene. Glad I stuck with it."</span>
