    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2560712572" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2560712572" />
    <a title="kartik narayanan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4070035-kartik-narayanan"><img alt="kartik narayanan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1521695201p2/4070035.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2560712572?book_show_action=true">Oct 15, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="kartik narayanan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="kartik narayanan" href="/user/show/4070035-kartik-narayanan">kartik narayanan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2560712572" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1121496362049584015">I am ashamed that it has taken me ages to find out about Harry Bosch. And to add insult to injury, I got to know this character through the Prime Video series. Well, I really liked the video series and so, I thought I would get into the books.<br/><br/>The Black Echo did not disappoint me in any way. I found it to be similar in tone, character and storyline with the video series. It is very noirish, hardboiled and has very convincing detective work. <br/>Now, I am no expert on crime but the way the detectives </span>
  <span id="freeText1121496362049584015" style="display:none">I am ashamed that it has taken me ages to find out about Harry Bosch. And to add insult to injury, I got to know this character through the Prime Video series. Well, I really liked the video series and so, I thought I would get into the books.<br /><br />The Black Echo did not disappoint me in any way. I found it to be similar in tone, character and storyline with the video series. It is very noirish, hardboiled and has very convincing detective work. <br />Now, I am no expert on crime but the way the detectives work in the books/series seems very down to earth and practical. There aren't any magical deductions based on evidence or personality like a Holmes or a Poirot. We don't get to hear the conclusion presented at the end of the book. This is about the journey of an investigation. The detectives grind through all the evidence, follow up on leads, do a lot of leg work and yes, some of them get insights some of the time. These are not earth shattering insights but rather, ones that bring together all the clues. <br /><br />The great thing about The Black Echo is that this mundane work is never boring. It managed to keep me riveted throughout the book. In addition, the multiple threads in the book intertwine seamlessly and make Harry's world rich and interesting. <br /><br />There is one gripe I have though, which is that I figured out who the bad guys were long before the conclusion. But this is minor when compared to the entire experience of the book.<br /><br />If you have watched season 3 of the prime video series, you can recognise that the main storyline is inspired from The Black Echo.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1121496362049584015" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


