    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_200459643" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/200459643" />
    <a title="Matt" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5903843-matt"><img alt="Matt" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1603562140p2/5903843.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/200459643?book_show_action=true">Aug 20, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Matt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Matt" href="/user/show/5903843-matt">Matt</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8130678-the-black-echo">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5903843-matt?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer200459643" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16835888538742995159">Having read most of Connelly&apos;s recent work (read: The Lincoln Lawyer series), I was pleased to take a step back in time and look at the early work of this great author. THE BLACK ECHO was the reader&apos;s intro to Harry Bosch, and it did not disappoint.<br/><br/>We learn a great deal about Bosch, as he is placed in the all too familiar lone detective who is fighting against a troubled past. Bosch comes upon a case that ends up having personal ties and fights to get justice for a former friend and Vietnam vet.</span>
  <span id="freeText16835888538742995159" style="display:none">Having read most of Connelly's recent work (read: The Lincoln Lawyer series), I was pleased to take a step back in time and look at the early work of this great author. THE BLACK ECHO was the reader's intro to Harry Bosch, and it did not disappoint.<br /><br />We learn a great deal about Bosch, as he is placed in the all too familiar lone detective who is fighting against a troubled past. Bosch comes upon a case that ends up having personal ties and fights to get justice for a former friend and Vietnam vet. Connelly takes us on many a trip through Bosch's past and lays the groundwork for what will soon become a very complex and thoroughly enjopyable character.<br /><br />I enjoyed this early foray into Connelly's mindset as an author and can only hope that this is a springboard of great things to come. Not as sarcastic as a John Corey (Nelson DeMille), or as family-centred as Alex Cross (James Patterson), Harry Bosch comes with his own baggage, some of which that the reader must unpack and keep in storage for future books.<br /><br />Well done, Mr. Connelly. I look forward to the rest of the series.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16835888538742995159" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

